  "title": "Plotting a Slave Rescue Over Corellian Hooch",
  "summary": "Aboard the Templar, Colonel Eckhart relaxes the duty roster and breaks out a case of cheap Corellian hooch for an all-hands meeting in the hangar following a successful raid on a pirate base. Chief engineer Druze briefs the crew on data swiped from the base, revealing that the freed captives were trafficking victims and that the operation runs frequent chop-shop trips to Nar Shaddaa for the Hutts. Amid running jokes about the ship's strict no-pets rule and the kittens Siarra wishes she could keep, the crew turns to planning. The Wroonian Kelnas, drawing on his criminal past, identifies likely starship yards on Nar Shaddaa and volunteers for an intelligence run with Druze, over Eckhart's flat rejection of his half-joking plan to be captured with a tracker. The team settles on a stealth approach: gather intel with a small disguised team, plan a surgical strike to free the slaves and leave no witnesses, and arrange covert transport via Tiaryn rather than the conspicuous Templar.",
